HunterSkill_002.name: Critical Boost
HunterSkill_002.explain: Increases the damage of critical hits.

HunterSkill_005.name: Fire Attack
HunterSkill_005.explain: Increases fire element attack power. (Elemental attack power has a maximum limit.)

HunterSkill_006.name: Water Attack
HunterSkill_006.explain: Increases water element attack power. (Elemental attack power has a maximum limit.)

HunterSkill_007.name: Ice Attack
HunterSkill_007.explain: Increases ice element attack power. (Elemental attack power has a maximum limit.)

HunterSkill_008.name: Thunder Attack
HunterSkill_008.explain: Increases thunder element attack power. (Elemental attack power has a maximum limit.)

HunterSkill_009.name: Dragon Attack
HunterSkill_009.explain: Increases dragon element attack power. (Elemental attack power has a maximum limit.)

HunterSkill_010.name: Poison Attack
HunterSkill_010.explain: Increases the rate of poison buildup. (Poison buildup has a maximum limit.)

HunterSkill_011.name: Paralysis Attack
HunterSkill_011.explain: Increases the rate of paralysis buildup. (Paralysis buildup has a maximum limit.)

HunterSkill_012.name: Sleep Attack
HunterSkill_012.explain: Increases the rate of sleep buildup. (Sleep buildup has a maximum limit.)

HunterSkill_013.name: Blast Attack
HunterSkill_013.explain: Increases the rate of blast buildup. (Blast buildup has a maximum limit.)

HunterSkill_003.name: Critical Element
HunterSkill_003.explain: Increases elemental damage (fire, water, thunder, ice, dragon) when landing critical hits.

HunterSkill_014.name: Handicraft
HunterSkill_014.explain: Extends the weapon sharpness gauge. However, it will not increase the gauge past its maximum.

HunterSkill_004.name: Master's Touch
HunterSkill_004.explain: Prevents your weapon from losing sharpness during critical hits.

HunterSkill_019.name: Ballistics
HunterSkill_019.explain: Extends the range in which ammo and arrows have maximum power.

HunterSkill_068.name: Divine Blessing
HunterSkill_068.explain: Has a predetermined chance of reducing the damage you take.

1.name: Divine Blessing
1.explain: While active, reduces damage taken by 15%.

2.name: Divine Blessing
2.explain: While active, reduces damage taken by 30%.

3.name: Divine Blessing
3.explain: While active, reduces damage taken by 50%.

1.name: Stun Resistance
1.explain: Reduces the duration of stun by 30%.

2.name: Stun Resistance
2.explain: Reduces the duration of stun by 60%.

HunterSkill_070.name: Recovery Speed
HunterSkill_070.explain: Speeds healing of recoverable damage (the red portion of the Health Gauge).

1.name: Recovery Speed
1.explain: Doubles the speed at which you heal recoverable damage.

2.name: Recovery Speed
2.explain: Triples the speed at which you heal recoverable damage.

3.name: Recovery Speed
3.explain: Quadruples the speed at which you heal recoverable damage.

HunterSkill_095.name: Bombardier
HunterSkill_095.explain: Increases the damage of explosive items.

HunterSkill_099.name: Free Meal
HunterSkill_099.explain: Gives you a predetermined chance of consuming a food or drink item for free.

HunterSkill_046.name: Speed Sharpening
HunterSkill_046.explain: Speeds up weapon sharpening when using a whetstone.

1.name: Speed Sharpening
1.explain: Removes one cycle from the sharpening process.

2.name: Speed Sharpening
2.explain: Removes two cycles from the sharpening process.

3.name: Master Mounter
3.explain: Makes it easier to mount monsters.

3.name: Master Gatherer
3.explain: Increases gathering speed, and prevents knock back when gathering or carving.

3.name: Fortify
3.explain: Increases attack and defense after fainting during a quest. (Can be used twice. Does not apply to some quests)

2.name: Powerhouse I
2.explain: Temporarily increases attack +10 after a successful Power Clash or Offset attack

4.name: Powerhouse II
4.explain: Temporarily increases attack +25 after a successful Power Clash or Offset attack
